🚀 Run Jenkins with access to Docker

🛠️ Shortcut: Auto-remove if it exists
If you want to overwrite without typing stop/rm every time, you can do:

# Create folder for Jenkins home
mkdir -p $(pwd)/jenkins_home

# Give full read/write permissions (safe for local dev)
chmod -R 777 $(pwd)/jenkins_home

# Run container
docker run -d \
  --name jenkins-dotnet9 \
  --platform=linux/amd64 \
  -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 \
  -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
  --user root \
  jenkins-dotnet9 
